Louder. Who can hear you?

292
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:54,960
Godfather.

293
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,120
Come here.

294
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,360
Let me hug you.

295
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,760
My darling.

296
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:03,480
How's my boy?

297
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:05,440
He will certainly grow up to be a man much better
  than you.

298
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,480
Of course.

299
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,120
Godfather.

300
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:12,040
Mom said dad won't return forever.

301
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:13,800
Is it true?

302
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,280
Yes.

303
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,680
But what if I miss him?

304
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:20,880
Then come to me.

305
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:21,520
Okay?

306
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:25,920
Can you play with me?

307
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:27,120
Of course, I can.

308
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:31,240
Can you teach me how to climb just like dad did?

309
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,400
Of course.

310
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,720
Let's go now.

311
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:35,800
Now?

312
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:37,400
OK.

313
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,640
Let's go.

314
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,480
Be good, Zanzan.

315
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:48,320
Songyang cares about you a lot.

316
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,680
How do you know?

317
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,880
He looks at you before making a promise.

318
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:55,240
That means he cares about you.

319
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:56,840
Nothing escapes your eyes, Li.

320
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,440
You have an eye for detail.

321
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,200
Do you support him in rock climbing?

322
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,120
Did Yu Songyang tell you something?

323
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,160
It's not like that.

324
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:06,720
I was just randomly asking.

325
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,440
Because...

326
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:09,040
You know it, right?

327
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,560
Zhiyuan fell right in front of him.

328
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,320
So,

329
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:17,320
do you think it's okay if he keeps doing extreme sports?

330
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,600
To tell you the truth,

331
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,400
I...

332
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,960
don't really support him.

333
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,520
Maybe I am not strong enough

334
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:29,600
to handle the burden.

335
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:30,440
So,

336
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:31,520
whenever I think about it,

337
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,560
I just...

338
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,120
If it was me,

339
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,800
I wouldn't have your reaction.

340
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,080
Do you mean I'm cold-blooded?

341
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,120
No.

342
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,080
No. I didn't mean that.

343
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:42,600
Li.

344
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,230
It's alright.

345
00:15:43,230 --> 00:15:44,880
There's nothing wrong with thinking like that.

346
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,520
You have the most normal way of thinking.

347
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:49,240
Indeed,

348
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,480
this is not easy.

349
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,880
On the day of the accident,

350
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:54,780
I was indeed struck

351
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:55,320
the moment

352
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,320
I went there.

353
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,880
I stood there and couldn't move.

354
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:00,440
I was just there with my mind completely blank.

355
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:01,240
I didn't have time

356
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,240
to cry or to do anything.

357
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:03,440
I was so,

358
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,080
so scared.

359
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,960
When did I start to recover a bit?

360
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,960
It was when I got back home and started to pack his stuff.

361
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,280
When I looked at his equipment,

362
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,520
his clothes

363
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:18,200
and the photos of rock climbing on his phone,

364
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,280
that was the time

365
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,360
I felt

366
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,320
that perhaps

367
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:24,960
he is gone.

368
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,720
I'm alright.

369
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,000
Indeed,

370
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,160
it was difficult to accept in the beginning.

371
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,240
However,

372
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:37,240
it's not an easy thing anyways.

373
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:42,360
I think you have a relatively good mindset.

374
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,200
I feel alright.

375
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,600
Sometimes, I'm good.

376
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,160
How did you manage to bounce back?

377
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,640
How is it possible to bounce back from something 
 like this?

378
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,960
I didn't mean to leave it behind.

379
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,200
I just had to leave it behind.

380
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,120
What do you think I can do?

381
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,120
I still have a kid to bring up.

382
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,920
I have to cook on time

383
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:00,360
and send him to school on time.

384
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,360
There's no other way.

385
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:04,400
Alright.

386
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,280
No problem.

387
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:07,720
What else can I do when it falls on me?

388
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,240
Do you really not blame him?

389
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,440
He just

390
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:14,440
left, leaving you and the kid.

391
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:19,400
Well.

392
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,240
I can't blame him.

393
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:25,960
I don't blame him.

394
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,319
It's because

395
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,560
I understand him.

396
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,560
I understand what he thinks.

397
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:32,520
In my mind,

398
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,880
he is a hero.

399
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,520
In the past,

400
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,320
We told Zanzan

401
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,600
when he was young

402
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,600
that he has to learn

403
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,280
to make decisions for himself.

404
00:17:42,460 --> 00:17:43,560
After making the decision,

405
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,240
you can't regret it.

406
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,120
You have to take responsibility for the decisions

407
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:48,360
you make.

408
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,600
After Zhiyuan's accident, I asked Zanzan,

409
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,400
"Do you still

410
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:54,920
want to carry on with rock climbing?

411
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:58,200
If you tell me you don't want to do it anymore,

412
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,160
we will stop it.

413
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:00,360
I won't force you."

414
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,120
He said,

415
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:03,240
"No.

416
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:05,080
"Mom, I want to do it.

417
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:06,160
"I like it.

418
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,320
"When I grow up,

419
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:13,200
"I will conquer

420
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:15,400
"the mountains dad hasn't conquered."

421
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,320
That's what he said.

422
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,400
What else can I say?

423
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:22,640
The only thing I can do is to ask Songyang

424
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:25,800
to check if Zanzan has a talent for it.

425
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,560
If he is like his dad, then he can learn

426
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:28,440
and just do it.

427
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:32,840
Yes, step hard.

428
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,920
Come on, be quick.

429
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,480
When you were training with Zanzan,

430
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:58,560
Li told me a lot.

431
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,200
What did she say?

432
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,200
I won't tell you.

433
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:06,280
What do you think about Li?

434
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:09,960
Tell me the truth.

435
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:12,200
Do you really hope that I can support you

436
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,320
the way she supported Zhiyuan?

437
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:17,080
This question is a death trap.

438
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,240
Just tell me. I promise I won't be mad.

439
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:23,920
Of course, I hope that we can support

440
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,880
each other's hobbies.

441
00:19:26,030 --> 00:19:28,600
But we need time to see if things like this can 
 stand the test.

442
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:32,560
So?

443
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,200
So,

444
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,480
I think you did pretty well.

445
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:38,000
When I was training with Zanzan,

446
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,000
you didn't even stop me.

447
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,280
Don't butter me up.

448
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:43,040
I let you do that because of Zanzan.

449
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:44,960
Don't forget that you're in rehabilitation.

450
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,600
But I said I would quit dangerous stuff.

451
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,160
That's not dangerous.

452
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,320
You can't forbid me from that.

453
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:50,970
Very well.

454
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:52,200
You're pushing your luck.

455
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,240
You're trying indirect ways to get what you want, right?

456
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:55,920
If you want to climb rocks,

457
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,680
you're only allowed to play with Zanzan.

458
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,080
Alright.

459
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,800
I promise you.

460
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,760
Where are you going?

461
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:07,800
What do you think?

462
00:20:07,970 --> 00:20:09,410
Did you get a godson just like that?

463
00:20:09,410 --> 00:20:10,990
Don't you need to buy some gifts for him?

464
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:11,890
Shame on you, godfather.

465
00:20:11,890 --> 00:20:12,720
You're so stingy.

466
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:14,800
How thoughtful.

467
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:18,680
Hi, Ms. Bai.

468
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,120
Let me see.

469
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,000
What are you doing?

470
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,360
Who else sharpens the knife in front of customers?

471
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,520
It's just my habit.

472
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:28,240
Alright.

473
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:29,240
I won't sharpen it.

474
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:31,640
She can't tolerate any mistakes.

475
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:33,920
We know each other well.

476
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:34,960
I did it for his good.

477
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:37,600
If it was someone else, I would turn around and walk away.

478
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,120
You're absolutely right, Ms. Bai.

479
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:39,810
Alright.

480
00:20:39,810 --> 00:20:40,880
Which piece would you like?

481
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,200
This piece is tender.

482
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:44,320
Do you want beef or lamb?

483
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:47,760
You said you will teach me how to cook, right?

484
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,360
Let's buy anything easy to make.

485
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,440
Then we will steam a fish.

486
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,920
Let's go and buy fish.

487
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,040
Come on.

488
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:54,920
Alright. We'll go.

489
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,480
Don't sharpen the knife like that again.

490
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:56,880
Ms. Bai.

491
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,680
See you next time.

492
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:58,800
But this piece is really tender.

493
00:20:58,800 --> 00:20:59,280
Look.

494
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:01,400
You scared her away by sharpening the knife.

495
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,240
But I said I won't do it again.

496
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,800
Alright. We will be back next time.

497
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:05,600
Next time.

498
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,360
Come on.

499
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,280
See you next time.

500
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,080
Leave it here.

501
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,040
I'll do it.

502
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:16,680
Don't touch anything.

503
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:17,320
Stand over here.

504
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,120
Leave everything to me.

505
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:19,560
OK.

506
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:23,800
Today, you just have to talk and tell me what to do.

507
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:24,640
I'll do everything.

508
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:27,240
Hello, delivery.

509
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:30,920
Coming.

510
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:38,800
Where does it hurt?

511
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,000
Come here.

512
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,000
Are you alright?

513
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,320
- No. 
 - No.

514
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,280
Come here.

515
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,360
Slow down.

516
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:50,520
I have bandaged you up.

517
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,920
Get some good rest when you go home.

518
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:52,440
OK.

519
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,280
Hello, president.

520
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:53,840
Thanks, doctor.

521
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:54,450
Hi, Doctor Lv.

522
00:21:54,450 --> 00:21:55,160
Hi, Dong Peng.

523
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:57,120
You are here as well.

524
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,160
Ms. Bai.

525
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,400
This is Vice President Dong.

526
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:03,120
Thank you for coming here.

527
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:04,520
Don't worry. Sit, please.

528
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:06,520
I'm Doctor Lv's student.

529
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:07,800
I have to check on you.

530
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,400
The doctor says it's a fracture.

531
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,520
It's nothing serious.

532
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,800
I will be fine after resting for 10 to 15 days.

533
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,680
Indeed, the elderly

534
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:16,120
need to be more careful.

535
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:19,640
You need to eat more food with a good amount of calcium.

536
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,280
Women lack calcium more easily.

537
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:22,760
Yeah, sunbathe more.

538
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,360
You also need to do a bit of

539
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:26,120
easy exercise at normal times.

540
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:27,080
You're right.

541
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,160
I normally don't have enough exercise.

542
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,180
Looks like I have to work out more in the future.

543
00:22:31,180 --> 00:22:32,560
It's mainly my fault.

544
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:33,920
I didn't take care of her.

545
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:34,920
It's not like that.

546
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:36,240
Madam,

547
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,360
don't do any housework

548
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,360
